{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-tsx","path":"/texts/tipitaka/sutta-pitaka/samyutta-nikaya/SN5/8-sisupacalasutta/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>At Sāvatthī. </p>\n<p>Then the nun Sīsupacālā robed up in the morning …\nand sat at the root of a tree for the day’s meditation. </p>\n<p>Then Māra the Wicked went up to Sīsupacālā and said to her,\n“Nun, whose creed do you believe in?” </p>\n<p>“I don’t believe in anyone’s creed, sir.” </p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>“In whose name did you shave your head? <br>\nYou look like an ascetic, <br>\nbut you don’t believe in any creed. <br>\nWhy do you live as if lost?” </p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>“Followers of other creeds <br>\nare confident in their views. <br>\nBut I don’t believe in their teaching, <br>\nfor they’re no experts in the Dhamma. </p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>But there is one born in the Sakyan clan, <br>\nthe unrivaled Buddha, <br>\nchampion, dispeller of Māra, <br>\neverywhere undefeated, </p>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>everywhere freed, and unattached, <br>\nthe all-seeing seer. <br>\nHe has attained the end of all deeds, <br>\nfreed with the ending of attachments. <br>\nThat Blessed One is my Teacher, <br>\nand I believe in his instruction.” </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Then Māra the Wicked, thinking, “The nun Sīsupacālā knows me!” miserable and sad, vanished right there.</p>\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<p><a href=\"/texts/tipitaka/sutta-pitaka/samyutta-nikaya/SN5/9-selasutta/\">SN.5.9. Selāsutta (“With Selā”)</a></p>\n</div>","htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"At Sāvatthī. "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Then the nun Sīsupacālā robed up in the morning …\nand sat at the root of a tree for the day’s meditation. "}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","propertie